Setting up the database
-----------------------

These procedures assume you have a working installation of MySQL version 4.1 or above.

Execute the following commands:

  $ mysqladmin create phpa
  $ mysql -e 'GRANT ALL ON phpa.* TO phpa';
  $ mysqladmin reload

And you probably want to import some data:

  $ wget 
  $ gunzip -c phpa-db-dump.gz | mysql phpa